Imminent Collision dinner at @phenakite.la ✨ Best night. Best people. Me trying to eat my neighbor’s plate. The usual. ⁣
⁣
Congrats Hieu, Randall, and Michael on another amazing year and to Chef @mignardisesla for the meal of my whole life!

Thank you for all the love yesterday I felt every single second of it. My emo self is not going to talk about how I’m crying again because y’all already know. 🥹🦋 So lucky to have friends who will engage in my 8 page 2 day itinerary of activities without question. Love you all so much.

Last year these people, this project, and this city got me through one of the hardest times of my life. Unconditionally. New York kept my spirit alive in a way I still don’t understand. There were constant moments that felt like kismet letting me know that my dad was still in my orbit somewhere amongst the clouds. I was right where he wanted me to be. I’ll be able to talk about him one day and tell you about him. Grief is a powerful thing that has left me broken with a million questions, but also at the same time, able to love 10x harder. I will never ever forget summer 2022 in NY and the people who gave their heart and souls to this production. I love making movies for this very reason- a group of passionate people from different walks of life, energies, and all in various stages of life, coming together with the collective goal of telling a story. I can’t wait for you all to see #Shortcomings 💛

🦋 See you this spring. 2023.⁣
⁣

THE LOVE WAS REAL. THE BLINK AAGC ENERGY WAS UNBEATABLE.⁣ 💝🖤
⁣
Our first ever AAGC dance party with @ellenkimchee was so. much. fun. The idea was inspired by my dearest friend @thealiciahannah who recently took me to my first @blackpinkofficial concert in LA where A. my mind was blown and B. I got to witness how powerful it was to see four badass Asian women on a stadium stage completely in control and fully owning who they are. UNREAL. I left with so many new friends. On top of that I had a greater understanding of how groundbreaking it is to have a group like Blackpink and how we didn’t have anything like this when we were kids. Wanted to recreate that feeling for @asianamericangirlclub and wow did everyone hype each other up! 🥹 We are 100% making this a regular thing so let me know if you want in. 
⁣
Thank you Ellen for empowering us to bring out our inner kpop stars lol and teaching us the Pink Venom routine of our dreams, @dinykim owner of the fabulous @rutsdancestudio , our very own @sharlenepark for planning every inch of this day, the @ryucreative team, our co-teachers @sukiestyles @akaisha.g and all the AAPI owned brands who sent goodies @cocokind @gogreenme @drinksanzo @mustloveco 
⁣
My goal is to have more micro events this year to celebrate our beautiful lil community in all the ways so please reach out if you have a cuteeeee idea for something. Would love to hear it! 🫰

The story of how Shortcomings came to be is so indicative of Randall’s conviction and steadfast heart. 15 years he spent committed to making this movie happen, so struck by the thought provoking and flawed characters that @adriantomine (my fellow Japanese American brother) had written. He is a director who lets you play in the most freeing and fantastic of ways, while still staying committed to his exact vision and never straying from it. He’s one of the kindest people I know in this business and in life. Alongside the incredible @hieunho a longtime friend and creator of @imminentcollision. It’s my first time to @sundanceorg and I can’t imagine a better family to enter into this whirlwind with @shrrycola @justinmin + everyone who worked on this lil love fest. Here we come ✨ #Shortcomings @vanityfair @beccamford
Been waiting my whole life for a moment like this. Forever family 🫶 #Shortcomings @ Sundance  @sundanceorg

Community is everything. Growing and advocating for it has become such an important purpose for me. It’s one of those things where you can’t really pinpoint what you’ve been missing until you’ve found it. ⁣
⁣
For this Lunar New Year and the Year of the Rabbit, I am thrilled to share my passion, story, and @asianamericangirlclub with UGG Stories With Purpose series. Lunar New Year means many things, but above all, it’s about being proud of our different cultures and creating deeper connections with community. Together with @ugg , I am so proud to donate $10,000 to one of my favorite grassroots nonprofits, @teachaapi . Teach AAPI aims to create spaces where children, parents, and people who identify with an AAPI culture can find a sense of belonging, confidence and pride in themselves. My mom was a public-school special education teacher my entire life, so education and inclusivity will always be things I value. It’s vital to continue to be vocal about what we’re learning and advocating for in schools. ⁣
⁣
Thank you UGG for giving us this space to be ourselves and giveback to causes that will authentically shape our next generation of leaders. 🫶#FeelsLikeUGG Link in bio to read my story. 🐇 🧧
Thank you Sundance for an unforgettable weekend. Lots and lots of tears were shed. 🫶🥪 @sundanceorg

I DON’T HAVE WORDS. #TEAMAAGC MADE IT TO TIMES SQUARE!!!! When I think of where this all started, on my living room floor, with only a hope and dream of connecting the AAPI women around me, to what it is today. I shed a few tears. It’s all because of you. It’s because of the AAGC team past or current, who bring every ounce of passion to the table. It’s because of all the trailblazers who dare to go where we have never gone before. It’s because of everyone who reps AAGC with pride.⁣
⁣
The @asianamericangirlclub x @amazonmusic collaboration during AAPI Heritage Month means so much. It is such a powerful platform for underrepresented artists to be highlighted and celebrated. It is vital to help Asian and Asian American women see themselves as leaders in the music industry, and break the mold of what is possible. Music is a powerful tool, one that can shape culture and bridge gaps. Building connectivity amongst AAPI female artists and allies will always be an important aspect of this collaboration, as well as to Asian American Girl Club as a whole. Seeing artists like @hayleykiyoko, who empowers young people struggling with their sexuality, next to @rubyibarra, who inspires strength and resilience within the Filipino community, is powerful. Incredible artists like @thuymusic, @nikizefanya, and @yuna who inspire movements with their music. We hope that by seeing these trailblazing AAPI female artists, side by side on a billboard in the middle of Times Square, that you will see your potential as limitless. ⁣
⁣
Thank you @whatsgoodfrankie and the Amazon Music team for year two of this beautiful partnership! You steadfastly believe in our mission at AAGC and constantly advocate for greater opportunities for Asian and Asian American women and allies. It’s never taken for granted. #AAGCxAmazonMusic

So wonderful to speak on this panel in honor of AAPI Heritage Month for @goldhouseco x @appletv. We covered representation and playing Hana on #TheBigDoorPrize - a character brought to life by the minds of our brilliant writers and creator. The amount of love in that room coming from both emerging and established artists pursuing space in the entertainment industry was beautiful! ⁣

Honored to be an executive producer on @mimitieuvo and @titania.tran 3rd social impact film “My Sister.” The minute I met Mimi and T our hearts pulled towards each other with such instant connectivity. We knew we had to create something special. Mimi and T you leave an indelible mark on the world- I’m blown away by the way in which you merge powerful storytelling with activism. Thank you for having me be part of your process. Proud to call you my sisters. ⁣
⁣
like Mimi and Titania’s prior films, this was self-initiated, with no initial funding, and not tied to a brand. ⁣
it is a response to what is happening today. to the women of iran. the women of afghanistan. the women of the united states of america. the women of the world. ⁣
⁣
what of their safety? their education? their choice? ⁣
⁣
“my sister” amplifies how communities have mobilized, and recognizes those efforts not as isolated protests, but as a single, global revolution. this film is an effort to unify, and offer solidarity to those progressing this movement, by identifying them as we do in asian cultures:⁣
⁣
not as strangers, but as sisters. ⁣
——⁣

Our feature film ‘Seagrass’ had its World Premiere at @tiff_net and I am still overcome with emotion. From day 1, I felt a kinship with @meredithhamabrown that would continue to grow over the past two years. Mere is a filmmaker who is so special and steadfast with her vision, and executes with a beautifully focused passion and empathy. So in awe of her. Seagrass is a story that closely mirrors my family history, but further expanded my worldview to the Japanese Canadian experience during the 90’s. It’s a beautiful story of how intergenerational trauma is carried down to subsequent generations, specifically Japanese Canadians/Americans.⁣
⁣
Not only was I able to play the role of Judith, a name my real mother shares, it was my first time being an executive producer on a film. The experience was extraordinary. We shot entirely on film, a testament to our entire phenomenal cast and crew. Our brilliant young cast including @remymarthaller @blossomnyha @hannah_bos_official taught me more than I could ever know about staying present and finding beauty in the unknown. ⁣
⁣
I’ve found forever creative partners and friends in Meredith and @norm_li . They’re people you want to break bread with and pour your heart to. They’re people who care about making movies to move people. Love you both so much.⁣ 
⁣
We are in the midst of a very important time in our industry, breaking ground in vital ways for the necessary protection and equity of creatives. We are grateful to SAG-AFTRA for their permission and support of our film and for truly independent films overall. Independent films are our industry’s lifeblood, bringing new worldviews and oftentimes underrepresented narratives to the surface. *Credits in the caption*

An immense honor. Thank you @tiff_net for awarding @seagrassfilm and our visionary @meredithhamabrown the prestigious International Film Critics FIPRESCI Award for Best International First Feature. @fipresci 
⁣
Thank you to the FIPRESCI jury for honoring our film and director: Cem Altinsaray, Elijah Baron, Jindřiška Bláhová, Diego Faraone, and Jenni Zylka. Congrats to our entire cast and crew. Meredith and @norm_li , you deserve it all and I’m elated that the world is seeing your brilliance. ⁣
⁣
It was a dream come true to have our world premiere at TIFF and to have my mom there with me. 🤍⁣
in my mind I’m a teenager again watching New York minute and bedazzling my sidekick in my bedroom 🍎 NY you give me life

To our #TeamAAGC family,

Happy fifth birthday AAGC! Today, we celebrate not just a milestone, but the magic of five incredible years together. It feels unreal. My heart beams knowing that AAGC exists for anyone who has ever been looked over, felt underrepresented, or needed a friend to share the deepest parts of their soul with. In the work we do, the team constantly thinks about how we can change this statistic: Asian women are the least likely to be promoted to C-suite and executive level positions. This single quote motivates us every single day to continue to show how resilient we are. We are leaders and always have been.

We wanted to take this time to say thank you for being the heart and soul of AAGC. Your creativity and boundless enthusiasm have shaped us into the vibrant community we are today. Your unwavering support has allowed us to sustain a brilliant team (of wonderful humans!), plan events, design merch, giveback to help our community and others, and help us to continue to dream bigger for you all. For that, we are eternally grateful.

So cheers to you, AAGC. Here’s to many more years together. Here’s to the memories we’ve created, the friendships we’ve forged, and the dreams we’ve chased together. We are brimming with excitement (truly!) at everything we are planning for year six. We can’t do it without each and every single one of you. 
Let’s take AAGC all the way to the stars.

With love and endless gratitude,
Ally and the AAGC Team 💞

Feeling a little reflective on @asianamericangirlclub 5 year anniversary week 🥹 I’d be lying if I told you that building a community isn’t challenging. You’re living on blind faith and adrenaline. It’s nonstop and you feel like you can’t stop to take a breath because you don’t want to let anyone down. There’ve been times when I’ve wondered how we’re going to keep the lights on because I refuse to rush things or compromise one ounce of authenticity. Times where I’ve personally been so burnt out it’s taken a huge toll on my health. And all I wonder at night is how I’m going to keep this team going. Community building is this messy, all encompassing, beautiful whirlwind that sweeps you up. It feels like every moment is vital because it means so damn much to me. But through every season, time and time again, it’s been this community that has pulled through and shown up for us. We learn how to breathe again and show up for ourselves. ⁣
⁣
We’re entering into a beautiful season of AAGC…. one where we can just let it ride and trust that no matter what things will work out. Learning how to ask for more help. I’m so grateful for every single one of you who have helped us continue to push this beautiful boulder up the hill. And to the team (past present and future) I love you with my full heart. I promise you that I will never ever give up. x
